docs.abstract: The event marked the start of what looks to be a long and grueling Democratic primary season, as dozens of candidates eye joining the race.
docs.snippet: The event marked the start of what looks to be a long and grueling Democratic primary season, as dozens of candidates eye joining the race.
docs.lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Senator Elizabeth Warren hit the presidential campaign trail in southwestern Iowa on Friday evening, making her the first declared major candidate to host an event in the pivotal state and kicking off a Democratic primary season that promises to dominate the coming year.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Campaigns in Iowa: ‘This Is How It Starts’

docs.abstract: In the On Politics newsletter, why we need to throw away the cliches we use to describe candidates. Plus, recapping a busy day in Congress.
docs.snippet: In the On Politics newsletter, why we need to throw away the cliches we use to describe candidates. Plus, recapping a busy day in Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: Happy New Year! We hope you’re rested and ready for all that 2019 will bring. This is On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.

headline.main: Is ‘Likability’ in Politics Sexist? Yes. It’s Also Outdated.

docs.abstract: Mark Harris, a Republican who had looked like the winner in North Carolina’s disputed congressional election, says he finds himself in “no-man’s land.”

headline.print_headline: Winner in Disputed Race Petitions Court to Let Him Take His Seat Anyway

docs.abstract: A bill passed by the Republican-controlled House would punish groups for submitting incomplete voter registrations. Critics say it would stifle minority votes.
docs.snippet: A bill passed by the Republican-controlled House would punish groups for submitting incomplete voter registrations. Critics say it would stifle minority votes.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tennessee lawmakers passed a bill through the state House on Monday that would fine community groups that submit incomplete voter-registration applications, an unusual move that the bill’s opponents have denounced as voter suppression.

headline.main: Tennessee Advances Bill That Could Make It Harder to Register New Voters

docs.abstract: The government “has systematically discriminated against black people in this country,” the senator and likely presidential hopeful warned.
docs.snippet: The government “has systematically discriminated against black people in this country,” the senator and likely presidential hopeful warned.
docs.lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE — Senator Elizabeth Warren, in a commencement speech Friday at historically black Morgan State University, mixed her trademark language denouncing economic inequality with more explicit indictments of racial discrimination, giving what could be a preview of a possible appeal to black voters should she run for president.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren, Speaking to Black Graduates, Warns ‘the Rules Are Rigged’
headline.print_headline: Warren Tells Young Blacks:  ‘The Rules  Are Rigged’

docs.snippet: The former vice president, accused by Ms. Flores, a Nevada Democrat, of kissing and touching her, did acknowledge ‘expressions of affection’ on campaign trail.
docs.lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., under pressure to respond to allegations that he touched and kissed a former Nevada assemblywoman, Lucy Flores, went on the defensive Sunday morning with a sweeping statement saying he did not believe he acted inappropriately but acknowledging that he had made “expressions of affection” during his years on the campaign trail.

headline.main: Joe Biden Says He Did Not Act Inappropriately With Lucy Flores
headline.print_headline: Nevada Lawmaker Says Biden Kissed Her in 2014

docs.abstract: She called for the Democratic-led House to begin an impeachment effort based on evidence that Mr. Trump attempted to undermine the special counsel’s inquiry.
docs.snippet: She called for the Democratic-led House to begin an impeachment effort based on evidence that Mr. Trump attempted to undermine the special counsel’s inquiry.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren on Friday called for the Democratic-led House of Representatives to begin impeachment proceedings against President Trump, making her the most prominent Democrat to move toward ousting the president over evidence from the special counsel’s investigation that Mr. Trump attempted to undermine that inquiry.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Calls for Impeachment Process Against Trump
